# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Review

## Findings
1. [P2] Fix 1 not implemented — [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:5054) still hides the `"Другой запрос?"` control whenever any active `other` request exists via `!activeRequests.some(r => r.type === 'other') && !showOtherForm`. The required disabled-visible state is missing, no helper text is rendered, and the new `tr('help.other_only_one', ...)` key is absent from both translation objects. FIX: keep the existing `!showOtherForm` hide rule, but always render the link when the form is closed; compute `hasActiveOther`, switch the classes to the disabled visual (`text-gray-300`, no underline/hover, default cursor) when true, render the helper text under it, and add `help.other_only_one` to both EN and RU dictionaries.
2. [P2] Fix 2 stale timer text not implemented — [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1898) still returns raw minutes for every elapsed time after 60 seconds and never branches to `tr('help.stale_status', ...)`. A 24h+ request will therefore keep showing a large minute count instead of the required stale label. FIX: in `getHelpTimerStr`, add an early return for `elapsedSec >= 24 * 60 * 60` that returns `tr('help.stale_status', 'Данные могли устареть')`.
3. [P2] Fix 2 auto-resolve effect is missing — the Help drawer effect block around [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2742) only increments `timerTick`; there is no `useEffect` tied to `timerTick` that scans `activeRequests` and calls `handleResolve(type, id)` for rows older than 24 hours. Stale requests therefore remain active indefinitely. FIX: add a Help-scoped `useEffect` that runs on `timerTick`, filters `activeRequests` by `Date.now() - sentAt > 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000`, and resolves each stale row through local `handleResolve(type, otherId)` without introducing a new polling interval or backend call.
4. [P3] Fix 3 draft persistence on drawer close/open is not implemented — [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2357) resets `showOtherForm` and `helpComment` in `openHelpDrawer`, and [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2370) clears both again in `closeHelpDrawer`. There is no `sos_draft_${currentTableId}` save/restore effect around `isHelpModalOpen`, so closing the drawer by swipe or backdrop still discards the unsent textarea draft. FIX: add the requested `useEffect` for save/restore keyed by `isHelpModalOpen`, wrap `localStorage` access in `try/catch`, and skip restore when an active `other` request already exists.
5. [P3] Fix 3 draft cleanup paths are also missing — the Cancel button at [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:5077) only calls `setShowOtherForm(false); setHelpComment('');`, and the successful `other` send path clears UI state at [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2588) and [x.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:5121) without removing `sos_draft_${currentTableId}`. Once draft persistence is added, both flows would leave stale drafts behind. FIX: remove `localStorage` draft state on explicit cancel and on successful send, both behind `try/catch`.
6. [P2] Fix 4 HelpFab position has not changed — [HelpFab.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/HelpFab.jsx:7) still uses `right-4 md:right-8`, so the FAB remains on the bottom-right instead of the required bottom-left. FIX: replace only those classes with `left-4 md:left-8` and keep the rest of the component unchanged.

## Summary
Total: 6 findings (0 P0, 0 P1, 4 P2, 2 P3)

